Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Animate
    Animate extends Actor and includes overarching methods for the movement of all moving actors (Pacman and Ghosts).
    BigDot
    BigDot extends Edible and its purpose is to temporarily change the status of the world to hypeMode when eaten.
    BlueGhost
    BlueGhost extends Ghost.
    Dot
    Dot extends Edible and is meant to be eaten by Pacman.
    Edible
    Edible extends Actor and is an abstract class for items to be eaten by Pacman (Dot and BigDot).
    Gate
    Gate extends Wall is a special wall with different image that ghosts move through when they spawn.
    Ghost
    Ghost extends Animate and is the parent class for all ghosts.
    NotWall
    NotWall extends Actor and is an empty space which animate objects can move through.
    OrangeGhost
    OrangeGhost extends Ghost.
    Pacman
    Pacman, which extends Animate, is directly controlled by the user.
    Pacworld
    Pacworld extends World, a class that is imported from Greenfoot.
    PinkGhost
    PinkGhost extends Ghost.
    RedGhost
    RedGhost extends Ghost.
    ScoreCounter
    ScoreCounter extends Actor and increments and updates the score.
    StartSquare
    StartSquare extends NotWall and is the location Ghosts go to when spawning.
    Tester
    Tester for methods not testable by GUI (data structures, etc.)
    Wall
    Wall extends Actor and it establishes the boundaries for other actors.
